Read in data

hormone information

hormone_info <-
  read_xlsx(
    hormone_info_file, 
    sheet = "T1",
    na = c("999","888")
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    Assay_ID = as.numeric(Assay_ID),
    Corticosteroid = as.numeric(Corticosteroid)
  ) %>% 
  bind_rows(
    read_xlsx(
      hormone_info_file, 
      sheet = "TK1",
      na = c("999","888")
    )
  ) %>% 
  bind_rows(
    read_xlsx(
      hormone_info_file, 
      sheet = "Tmid",
      na = c("999","888")
    ) %>% 
      mutate(Assay_ID = as.numeric(Assay_ID))
  ) %>% 
  bind_rows(
    read_xlsx(
      hormone_info_file, 
      sheet = "T2",
      na = c("999","888")
    )
  ) %>% 
  bind_rows(
    read_xlsx(
      hormone_info_file, 
      sheet = "TK3",
      na = c("999","888")
    )
  ) %>% 
  bind_rows(
    read_xlsx(
      hormone_info_file, 
      sheet = "T3",
      na = c("999","888")
    )
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    timepoint = str_extract(Timepoint_ID, "T\\d|TK\\d|Tmid")
  ) %>% 
  rename_at(
    vars(-ELS_ID),
    str_to_lower
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    # convert hormone collection time to hours from 12AM
    time_collection = hour(time_collection) + minute(time_collection) / 60,
    ELS_ID = as.numeric(ELS_ID),
    # create 1/0 variable for medication
    medication_binary = if_else(
      str_detect(medication, "None"), 
      0, 1
    )
  ) %>% 
  select(
    ELS_ID,
    timepoint,
    everything(),
    -timepoint_id
  )

cortisol <-
  cortisol_data %>% 
  filter(!is.na(`Sample ID`), !is.na(`ELS ID`)) %>% 
  mutate(
    measure = "cortisol"
  ) %>% 
  select(
    path,
    ELS_ID = `ELS ID`,
    measure,
    assay_id = `Sample ID`,
    timepoint = Timepoint, 
    rep1 = `Rep 1`,
    rep2 = `Rep 2`,
    mean = `Mean (µg/dL)`
  )

dhea <-
  dhea_data %>% 
  mutate(
    measure = "dhea",
    ELS_ID = as.numeric(
      case_when(
        !is.na(`ELS ID`) ~ `ELS ID`
      )
    ),
    ELS_ID = round(ELS_ID, 2)
  ) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(`Sample ID`), !is.na(ELS_ID)) %>% 
  select(
    path,
    ELS_ID,
    measure,
    assay_id = `Sample ID`,
    timepoint = Timepoint,
    rep1 = `Rep 1`,
    rep2 = `Rep 2`,
    mean = `Mean (pg/mL)`
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    timepoint = if_else(
      is.na(timepoint),
      str_extract(ELS_ID, " Tmid"), timepoint
    ),
    ELS_ID = str_replace(ELS_ID, " Tmid", "")
    )

testos <-
  testosterone_data %>% 
  mutate(
    measure = "testosterone",
    ELS_ID = as.numeric(
      case_when(
        !is.na(`ELS ID`) ~ `ELS ID`
      )
    ),
    ELS_ID = round(ELS_ID, 2)
  ) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(`Sample ID`), !is.na(ELS_ID)) %>% 
  select(
    path,
    ELS_ID,
    measure,
    assay_id = `Sample ID`,
    timepoint = Timepoint,
    rep1 = `Rep 1`,
    rep2 = `Rep 2`,
    mean = `Mean (pg/mL)`
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    timepoint = if_else(
      is.na(timepoint),
      str_extract(ELS_ID, " Tmid"), timepoint
    ),
    timepoint = if_else(
      timepoint == "TMID",
      "Tmid", timepoint
    ),
    ELS_ID = str_replace(ELS_ID, " Tmid", "")
  )

Join all hormones

hormones_all <-
  testos %>% 
  bind_rows(dhea) %>% 
  bind_rows(estrad) %>% 
  bind_rows(progest) %>% 
  bind_rows(cortisol) %>% 
  mutate(
    comment = case_when(
      mean == "qns" | rep1 == "qns" | rep2 == "qns" ~ "qns",
      mean == "ND" | rep1 == "ND" | rep2 == "ND" ~ "none detected",
      str_detect(mean, "\\*") | str_detect(rep1, "\\*") | str_detect(rep2, "\\*")  ~ "mean/rep1/rep2 below lower limit or interference",
      TRUE ~ NA_character_
    ),
    timepoint = if_else(
      timepoint == "TMID" | timepoint == "Tmid",
      "Tmid", timepoint
    )
  ) %>% 
  # coercing hormone values to be numeric; will result in NAs for those
  # marked as "qns", "ND", "*" (below lower limit of sensitivity), or ** (interference likely)
  # those marked as above are noted in comments variables
  mutate_at(
    vars(
      ELS_ID, assay_id, rep1:mean
    ),
    as.numeric
  ) %>% 
  filter(ELS_ID != 7) #removing participant who withdrew
NAs introduced by coercionNAs introduced by coercionNAs introduced by coercion

Join with hormone master sheet

hormones <-
  hormones_all %>% 
  left_join(hormone_info, by = c("ELS_ID", "assay_id", "timepoint")) %>% 
  mutate(
    #create new variable to denote session type
    session_type = case_when(
      str_detect(ELS_ID, "\\.2") == TRUE ~ "second session",
      str_detect(ELS_ID, "\\.5") == TRUE ~ "session after braces",
      TRUE ~ "first session"
    ),
    #coerce ELS_ID to integer
    ELS_ID = as.integer(ELS_ID)
  ) %>% 
  select(
    path,
    ELS_ID,
    session_type, 
    everything()
  )

Winsorize hormone data within sex and timepoint to +/- 3SD value

hormones_clean <-
  hormones %>% 
  group_by(timepoint, male, measure) %>% 
  mutate_at(
    vars(
      rep1:mean
      ),
    funs("win" = winsorize), product = 3
  ) %>% 
  ungroup()
funs() is soft deprecated as of dplyr 0.8.0
Please use a list of either functions or lambdas: 

  # Simple named list: 
  list(mean = mean, median = median)

  # Auto named with `tibble::lst()`: 
  tibble::lst(mean, median)

  # Using lambdas
  list(~ mean(., trim = .2), ~ median(., na.rm = TRUE))

Log transform

hormones_clean <-
  hormones_clean %>% 
  group_by(timepoint, male, measure) %>% 
  mutate_at(
    vars(rep1_win:mean_win),
    funs(
      if_else(. == 0, NA_real_, .)
    )
  ) %>% 
  mutate_at(
    vars(rep1_win:mean_win),
    funs("log" = log)
  )

Select relevant columns, spread measure column, export

hormones_final <- 
  hormones_clean %>% 
  #rowid_to_column() %>% 
  mutate(
    birth_control = if_else(
      timepoint == "T1" & is.na(birth_control), 
      0, birth_control
    )
  ) %>% 
  select(
    ELS_ID,
    session_type,
    measure,
    timepoint,
    male,
    rep1:mean,
    rep1_win:mean_win,
    rep1_clean = rep1_win_log,
    rep2_clean = rep2_win_log,
    mean_clean = mean_win_log,
    comment,
    scan_date:birth_control,
    medication_binary
  ) %>% 
  gather(
    key, 
    value, 
    rep1, 
    rep2,
    mean,
    rep1_win,
    rep2_win,
    mean_win,
    rep1_clean,
    rep2_clean,
    mean_clean,
    comment
  ) %>% 
  unite("measure_key", measure, key) %>% 
  distinct(ELS_ID, measure_key, timepoint, session_type, .keep_all = TRUE) %>% 
  spread(measure_key, value) %>%
